l to Haskalah gave way to Jewish nationalism in the twentieth century.The readings in this book are theoretically informed, setting forward novel claims based on detailed textual analyses of Hasidic tales, Haskalah satires, and Zionist narratives. Thus, this book tackles a major interpretative problem visible at the core of modern Hebrew literature—its radical difficulty in distinguishing between the theological components of modern Jewish discourse and its national identity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aHasidimvLegends. 0aHasidimxLegendsxHistory and criticism. 0aHasidism. 0aHaskalah. 0aHebrew literature, ModernxHistory and criticism. 0aZionism in literature. 0aZionism. 7aHISTORY / Jewish.2bisacsh  aHasidic tales.  aHasidic.  aHasidism.  aHaskalah.  aHebrew literature.  aIsaac Erter.  aJewish Enlightenment.  aJewish Question.  aMicha Joseph Berdyczewski.  aModern Jewish literature.  aSefer Ḥasidim.  acultural history.  adiaspora.  aliterature.  amaskilic.  amaskilim.  amodernity.  anationalism.  anineteenth century.  apolitics.  apostcolonial theory.  arational, satire.  asecularization.  atranslation.  azionism.  azionist.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishz978311131913108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023z9783111318189oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Pennsylvania Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079137240uhttps://doi.org/10.9783/9781512825084?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/97815128